Error Reporting

For error reports or suggestions, please contact Frans Kaashoek and Robert Morris at kaashoek@mit.edu and rtm@mit.edu. The primary purpose of xv6 is to serve as a teaching operating system for MIT's course 6.1810. Simplifications and clarifications are prioritized over new features.

Building and Running xv6

To build and run xv6, you will need the RISC-V "newlib" toolchain, which can be obtained from the official RISC-V GNU Toolchain repository, and QEMU compiled for riscv64-softmmu. After installing these tools and ensuring they are in your system's search path, you can build and run xv6 by executing the make qemu command in the project directory.
